---
const stack = [
  ['Languages', 'Spanish · English'],
  ['Based in', 'Mexico City'],
  ['Sectors', 'Finance · Banking · SaaS · GovTech · Consulting · Startups'],
];
---

<section id="about" class="about">
  <div class="about-mark">
    <div class="about-eyebrow">About</div>
    <div class="about-monogram">
      M<sup class="about-c">C</sup>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="about-body">
    <p class="about-lead">
      Most of what lands on my desk arrives as somebody else's unfinished sentence — a vague ask, a half-built dataset, a problem nobody has named correctly yet. Job titles are bad predictors of what that kind of problem needs, and I've built a career on the mismatch: moving between data engineering, applied ML, and quantitative modeling because the question demanded it, not because I collect skills. I work autonomously by default, but autonomy that doesn't end in a team agreeing on the outcome isn't autonomy — it's just noise with good intentions.
    </p>
    <p class="about-paragraph">
      What I actually want is for the thing to get used. A model, a pipeline, an analysis — the point isn't that it's elegant, it's that it changes what someone does on Monday, and, if I'm honest, a little of how we understand the world too. That's the only rent I trust.
    </p>
    <dl class="about-stack">
      {stack.map(([k, v]) => (
        <div>
          <dt>{k}</dt>
          <dd>{v}</dd>
        </div>
      ))}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about {
    padding: 96px var(--gutter-desktop);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr;
    gap: 48px;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .about {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      padding: 64px var(--gutter-mobile);
      gap: 32px;
    }
  }

  .about-mark {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .about-monogram {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 80px;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-top: 24px;
    font-weight: 400;
  }
  .about-c {
    font-size: 0.4em;
    color: var(--oxblood);
    margin-left: 4px;
  }

  .about-body {
    max-width: 40rem;
  }

  .about-lead {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 21px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: none; /* fill .about-body — must match the stack rule width */
    text-align: justify;
    hyphens: auto;
  }

  .about-paragraph {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin-top: 24px;
    max-width: none; /* fill .about-body — must match the stack rule width */
    text-align: justify;
    hyphens: auto;
  }

  .about-stack {
    margin: 48px 0 0 0;
    padding-top: 20px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto auto 1fr;
    gap: 24px 40px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .about-stack {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
  .about-stack dt {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .about-stack dd {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 8px 0 0 0;
  }
</style>
